---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 10
  Paragraph: 18
Title: Rifling Trunks
---
From the Three Dynasties on down, it has been this and nothing
else-shoving aside the pure and artless people and delighting in busy,
bustling flatterers; abandoning the limpidity and calm of inaction and
delighting in jumbled and jangling ideas. And this jumble and jangle
has for long confused the world.
